LIAR: A BENCHMARK DATASET FOR FAKE NEWS DETECTION

William Yang Wang, "Liar, Liar Pants on Fire": A New Benchmark Dataset for Fake News Detection, to appear in Proceedings of the 55th Annual Meeting of the Association for Computational Linguistics (ACL 2017), short paper, Vancouver, BC, Canada, July 30-August 4, ACL.
=====================================================================
Description of the TSV format:

Column 1: the ID of the statement ([ID].json).	（陈述ID）
Column 2: the label.							（标注）
Column 3: the statement.						（陈述）
Column 4: the subject(s).						（主题/类别）
Column 5: the speaker.							（发言者）
Column 6: the speaker's job title.				（发言者的工作标题）
Column 7: the state info.						（州的信息）
Column 8: the party affiliation.				（党派关系）
Column 9-13: the total credit history count, including the current statement.（发言者的信用历史数量）
9: barely true counts.							（真的数量）
10: false counts.								（假的数量）
11: half true counts.							（一半是真的的数量）
12: mostly true counts.							（大多为真的数量）
13: pants on fire counts.						（彻头彻尾的谎言的数量）
Column 14: the context (venue / location of the speech or statement).（陈述或演讲地址）

Note that we do not provide the full-text verdict report in this current version of the dataset,
but you can use the following command to access the full verdict report and links to the source documents:
wget http://www.politifact.com//api/v/2/statement/[ID]/?format=json

======================================================================
